<sect1 id="sec.ha.geo.oview">
 <title>Example Scenario and Basic Steps&mdash;Overview</title>
 <para>In the following sections, we will use an example scenario as outlined
  below:</para>
 <example id="ex.ha.geo.example2">
  <title>Scenario with a Two-Site Cluster, one Arbitrator, and Data Replication via DRBD</title>
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
    <para>A &geo; cluster with two sites, <literal>&cluster1;</literal> and
     <literal>&cluster2;</literal>, and one arbitrator.</para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>Each site has a private network routed to the other site: </para>
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>&cluster1;: <literal>192.168.201.x</literal>
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>&cluster2;: <literal>192.168.202.x</literal>
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>Each site runs a two-node cluster:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>cluster 
       <literal>&cluster1;</literal> consists of the nodes <literal>&node1;</literal> and <literal>&node2;</literal></para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>cluster <literal>&cluster2;</literal> consists of the nodes <literal>&node3;</literal> and 
       <literal>&node4;</literal></para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>Data is replicated across the sites with DRBD in asynchronous mode for disaster recovery.</para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>The booth configuration and other important configuration files are synchronized across the
     cluster sites and the arbitrator using &csync;.</para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
 </example> 
 
 <para>
 Setting up this scenario takes the following basic steps:
 </para>
 <variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
   <!--Setting Up the Booth Services-->
   <term><xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth" xrefstyle="select:title"/>
   </term>
   <listitem>
    <orderedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>Choosing whether to use the <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.default"
        xrefstyle="select:title"/> or a <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.multi"
        xrefstyle="select:title"/>. </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <!--sync booth config-->
      <para>
       <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.sync" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.
      </para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>Configuring the cluster resources for booth as explained in <xref
        linkend="sec.ha.geo.rsc.booth" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <!--Transferring the Resource Configuration to Other Cluster Sites -->
      <para><xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.rsc.sync.cib" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para></listitem>
     <listitem>
      <!--start boothd-->
      <para>
       <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.setup.booth.service"
        xrefstyle="select:title"/>.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
   <!--Setting Up DRBD-->
   <term><xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.drbd" xrefstyle="select:title"/></term>
   <listitem>
    <orderedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>Configuring DRBD as described in <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.drbd.cfg"
        xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>Configuring the cluster resources for DRBD as explained in
        <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.rsc.drbd" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <!--Transferring the Resource Configuration to Other Cluster Sites -->
      <para><xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.rsc.sync.cib" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>Synchronizing DRBD configuration files as shown in
       <xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.sync.csync2.start" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.</para>
     </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
   <!-- Synchronizing Configuration Files Across All Sites and Arbitrators   -->
   <term><xref linkend="sec.ha.geo.sync" xrefstyle="select:title"/></term>
   <listitem>
    <orderedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>Setting up &csync; as explained in <xref
        linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.sync.csync2.setup" xrefstyle="select:title"
       />.</para>
     </listitem>
     <listitem>
      <para>Initially synchronizing all relevant configuration files across the
       sites and arbitrators as described in <xref
        linkend="sec.ha.geo.booth.sync.csync2.start" xrefstyle="select:title"
       />.</para>
     </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
